            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when this window's project file has been modified by an outside source. This executes a dialog informing the user of this fact and reloads the project if the user chooses to do so.</description>
              <name>projectFileChanged</name>
              <operation>Create a new message box that informs the user the project file has changed and asks the user if they want to reload the project or ignore it.</operation>
              <operation>Execute the message box and check to see if they chose to reload the project.</operation>
              <operation>Reload the project by creating a new project with the same file path and setting this window's project to the reloaded one.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
