          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates this window's title, including the project name if it has one.</description>
              <name>updateTitle</name>
              <operation>If this window has a project then set the window title with the project name else just set it to the application's name.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates some of this window's actions by enabling or disabling them based off aspects of this window's project.</description>
              <name>updateActions</name>
              <operation>Enable or disable the save action based off this window's project.</operation>
              <operation>Enable or disable all other relevant actions based off this window having a project or not.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Makes sure this window's project has no unsaved changes and is OK to be closed, returning true if it is OK. If this window has no project then true is also returned. If this window's project has unsaved changes then the user is prompted to save it, cancel, or discard changes.</description>
              <name>isOkToClose</name>
              <operation>If this window has no project or the project is not modified then return that it is OK.</operation>
              <operation>Create a message box that queries the user about what to do with this window's project's unsaved changes.</operation>
              <operation>Execute the message box and get the user's response.</operation>
              <operation>If this window's project is new then attempt to save as else attempt to save.</operation>
              <operation>If the user choose cancel then return that it is not OK else the user choose discard so return that it is OK.</operation>
              <return_description>True if it is OK to close this window's current project or this window has no project, else false is returned.</return_description>
              <type>bool</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Saves this window's project to a new file location queried by presenting a file dialog to the user, returning true on success. If this window has no project, the file dialog fails execution, or saving the project throws an exception then false is returned.</description>
              <name>saveAs</name>
              <operation>Make sure this window has a project to save.</operation>
              <operation>Create a new file dialog to query the user for a file path to save this window's project.</operation>
              <operation>Execute the file dialog and make sure it returned accepted.</operation>
              <operation>Get the first file path from the file dialog chosen by the user.</operation>
              <operation>Attempt to save this window's project to the file path.</operation>
              <operation>Update this window's actions and return success.</operation>
              <operation>If an exception was thrown then report it to the user and return false.</operation>
              <return_description>True if this window's project was successfully saved to a new location or false otherwise.</return_description>
              <type>bool</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Saves this window's project to its file, returning true on success or false on failure. If this window has no project then false is returned.</description>
              <name>save</name>
              <operation>Make sure this window has a project to save.</operation>
              <operation>Attempt to save this window's project.</operation>
              <operation>Return success.</operation>
              <operation>If an exception was thrown then report it to the user and return false.</operation>
              <return_description>True if the project was successfully saved or false otherwise.</return_description>
              <type>bool</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
