      <class>
        <data>
          <description>This is the access block. This represents access types for C++ classes such as public or private. This also defines Qt access types for slots and signals. Almost all block types used with classes must be attached to an access block instead of direct attachment because of how C++ works. All supported types are public, protected, private, signals, public slots, protected slots, and private slots.</description>
          <name>Access</name>
          <qtobject/>
        </data>
